scorecard.filtered <- scorecard %>%
  mutate(State = STABBR) %>%
  select(INSTNM, State, CONTROL, ADM_RATE, C150_4) %>%
  filter(CONTROL == 1 | CONTROL == 2) %>%
  na.omit()

scorecard.quant <- scorecard.filtered %>%
  select(CONTROL, ADM_RATE, C150_4)
scorecard4CL <- kmeans(scorecard.quant, centers = 4)
plot(scorecard.quant, col = scorecard4CL$cluster)

dis = dist(scorecard.quant)^2
sil = silhouette(scorecard4CL$cluster, dis)
fviz_silhouette(sil)
##   cluster size ave.sil.width
## 1       1  171          0.57
## 2       2  516          0.63
## 3       3  535          0.89
## 4       4  402          0.24

fviz_nbclust(scorecard.quant, kmeans, method = "wss") # determines the number of clusters

When cleaning the college scorecard, I decided to use CONTROL (public, private non-profit, or private for-profit), admit rate, and completion rate as my factors for clustering. I also omitted any empty data points, along with all for-profit institutions. Then, I constructed a 4-cluster model to see how the silhouette turned out, but used the fviz_nbclust function to determine the ideal number of clusters. My model is certainly limited in its interpretation, since it only considers admit rate, completion rate, and public vs. private institution.
